Practical guidance
If your goal is:

Gradual move to UE/EDS

Keep existing sections on Page Editor.
Stand up new sections (blog, campaigns, microsites) on UE/EDS.
Unify navigation/branding at the design/CDN level.
Single page “hybrid”

Today: don’t do it. Use separate pages and route between them instead.
If you absolutely must embed, treat the “other” stack as an external app (iframe/remote app) and accept that authors will edit that piece in its own editor, not as one seamless UE + Page Editor experience.


A single EDS setup can absolutely host:
Site A: doc-based authoring
Site B: UE/AEM authoring
(and even other sources like CFs or headless)
