Optional description. Add an Edge Delivery site to Cloud Manager

Verify repo ownership (one‑time)

Cloud Manager generates a token + path:

Add file in your repo:


Copy
well-known/adobe/cloudmanager-challenge.txt
(note: well-known, no dot) AEMaaCS Edge Delivery Services in Cloud Manager

Put CM‑provided token in that file.

Commit to main and click Verify.

When CM can read that file at your .aem.page URL, the site shows a green check. Add an Edge Delivery site to Cloud Manager, Cloud Manager - Support for EDS sites - AR

Attach domain + SSL + Adobe Managed CDN

From the same program:

Add Domain (e.g. www.example.com) in Cloud Manager.
Add SSL certificate (Adobe‑managed DV or your own OV/EV).
Create Domain Mapping:
CDN type: Adobe Managed CDN
Origin: your Edge Delivery site entry (backed by your .aem.live origin) AEMaaCS Edge Delivery Services in Cloud Manager, Edge Delivery Services deployment options in Adobe Managed CDN (in Cloud Manager)
Finally, update DNS to CNAME your domain to Adobe’s edge hostname (e.g. cdn.adobeaemcloud.com). Cloud Manager Self‑service access to Edge Delivery Services and Adobe Managed CDN

At this point:

Your .aem.page / .aem.live URLs keep working as before.
https://www.example.com is served via Adobe Managed (Fastly) CDN, fronting that same origin.
Does it matter if the site uses UE vs Docs vs DA?
No.

Cloud Manager and the CDN see only:

the Edge Delivery origin (main--repo--owner.aem.live) and
your domains + SSL.
Whether that origin is fed by:

UE + AEM Author, or
Doc Authoring (GDrive/SharePoint), or
DA.Live / Author Bus
…is irrelevant to the onboarding + CDN mapping flow. Crosswalk - Documentation - General (title tbd), Edge Delivery Services - Delivery Runbooks

Key constraints to keep in mind
You must have an Edge Delivery Services license to use the Cloud Manager + Adobe Managed CDN route; otherwise, you stay in BYO CDN land pointing directly at .aem.live. Cloud Manager Self‑service access to Edge Delivery Services and Adobe Managed CDN
Onboarding an existing repo/site is a first‑class path (“Add existing Edge Delivery site”) – you don’t have to recreate the site from scratch. Add an Edge Delivery site to Cloud Manager, Edge Delivery Services go‑live with your site
